# Git Workflow

## Branch Naming
`feature/`, `fix/`, `refactor/`, `docs/` + short kebab-case description
e.g. `feature/flaw-comment-pagination`, `fix/cvss-score-display`

## Commit Messages
Format: `<gitmoji> <short imperative sentence>`

| Type | Gitmoji |
|------|---------|
| New feature | вңЁ |
| Bug fix | рҹҗӣ |
| Refactor | вҷ»пёҸ |
| Tests | вң… |
| Docs | рҹ“қ |
| Chore/deps | рҹ”§ |
| Security | рҹ”’ |
| Performance | вҡЎ |
| Types | рҹҸ·пёҸ |

Examples:
- `вңЁ add pagination to flaw comment list`
- `рҹҗӣ fix CVSS score not updating on NVD import`
- `вҷ»пёҸ extract comment parsing into useFlawComments composable`

## PR Standards
- Group related commits; minimize count before push
- Run `yarn vibe-check` before opening PR
- Reference issue/ticket in PR description
